  "text": "n + 3/2 n + 2 + log 2 2 B (n + 1) (49) results, which reduces to B + log 2 (n) when the number of participating users is large. Therefore, multiuser selection policy based on SIR CQI provides a logarithmic increase in limiting achievable rate [CITATION_1] . This is in contrast to previous findings, where system rate improvement due to multiuser diversity effect was only by a factor of a double logarithm with respect to the number of users.",
